{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require 48 hours\u2019 notice before a \u2018dangerous dog\u2019 can be destroyed\r\n",
        "additional_details": "May dog owners may not know their rights when the police determine a dog is a prohibited breed. This can lead to owners feeling scared or intimidated into signing over their dog to be destroyed.\r\n \r\nA 48 hour period needs to be in place from the moment their dog is seized under the Dangerous Dogs Act before destruction can take place.",
        "background": "Too many people risk losing their beloved family dog by not knowing their rights at the time their dog is seized. The law should be changed so that dog owners are given 48 hours\u2019 notice before their dog can be destroyed.",
